label.value: Advanced Research Projects Agency for Health

value.value: An agency created to improve the United States government's ability to expedite health research and innovate the process of preventing, treating and possibly curing disease. It was enacted by Public Law 117-103 on March 15, 2022, which authorized the establishment of ARPA-H within the U.S. Department of Health and Human Services (HHS).
